In 1989, they self-released a demo tape and this led to a seven-inch EP called Words of War a year later through Vegan Reich's own label, Hardline Records.
The recordings were released by Hardline Records as the posthumous Above The Law LP and CD in 1994.
This was later re-released in 1995 by Victory Records as the Hands off The Animals CD.
